  <div style="max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 26px 32px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; width: 945px; height: 106px">
      
      <span style="font-size: 30px; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: 1.4px; color: #16203A; text-align: center; width: 909px; height: 93px; font-family: newsreader serif; font-style: italic"><h2 style="font-family: &quot;Public Sans&quot;, system-ui, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.12; letter-spacing: -1.2px; margin: 0px 0px 22px; width: 890px; height: 53px"><br>grounded in movement disorder care.</h2></span><div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:40px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
        
        
        
        
      </div>
    </div></div>

  <!-- PROBLEM -->
  <div style="max-width:1000px; margin:0 auto; padding:96px 32px 30px; text-align:center;">
    <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:16px;">THE PROBLEM</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,5.6vw,46px); line-height:1.12; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-1.2px; margin:0 0 22px;">Parkinson's doesn't keep a schedule,<br>So why does the pill bottle?</h2>
    <p style="font-size:20px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; max-width:680px; margin:0 auto;">Medication works until it doesn't. As the day goes on, <span style="font-weight:700; color:#16203A;">on</span> time gets shorter and <span style="font-weight:700; color:#8A4B00;">off</span> periods, stiffness, slowness, tremor, arrive earlier than the clock predicts. Fixed dosing times can't keep up with a body that shifts hour to hour.</p>
  </div>
  <div style="max-width:880px; margin:0 auto 90px; padding:0 32px;">
    <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:26px; padding:30px 30px 24px; box-shadow:0 18px 40px rgba(28,46,92,0.06);">
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; font-size:13px; font-weight:700; color:#8A96B0; margin-bottom:10px;"><span>8 AM</span><span>12 PM</span><span>4 PM</span><span>8 PM</span></div>
      <div style="display:flex; height:46px; border-radius:13px; overflow:hidden;">
        <div style="width:30%; background:#1F8A5B;"></div>
        <div style="width:7%; background:repeating-linear-gradient(45deg,#E8A23D,#E8A23D 6px,#F3CE92 6px,#F3CE92 12px);"></div>
        <div style="width:22%; background:#1F8A5B;"></div>
        <div style="width:9%; background:repeating-linear-gradient(45deg,#E8A23D,#E8A23D 6px,#F3CE92 6px,#F3CE92 12px);"></div>
        <div style="width:18%; background:#1F8A5B;"></div>
        <div style="width:14%; background:repeating-linear-gradient(45deg,#E8A23D,#E8A23D 6px,#F3CE92 6px,#F3CE92 12px);"></div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:26px; margin-top:16px; flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:8px;"><span style="width:13px; height:13px; border-radius:4px; background:#1F8A5B;"></span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#3A4A66;">On, moving freely</span></div>
        <div style="display:flex; align-items:center; gap:8px;"><span style="width:13px; height:13px; border-radius:4px; background:#E8A23D;"></span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#3A4A66;">Off, symptoms return</span></div>
        <span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:500; color:#8A96B0; margin-left:auto;">Off windows creep earlier through the day.</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TWO SYMPTOMS -->
  <div style="max-width:1100px; margin:0 auto 30px; padding:0 32px;">
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:24px;" data-stack="1">
      <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:26px; padding:34px 32px; box-shadow:0 14px 34px rgba(28,46,92,0.05);">
        <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:#B9700F; margin-bottom:14px;">SYMPTOM ONE · TIMING</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:26px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.5px; margin:0 0 12px;">off episodes</h3>
        <p style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0;">the dose wears off before the next one is due and symptoms return, stiffness, slowness, tremor. absorption shifts with meals and gut speed, so the same pill at the same time lands differently from one day to the next. most people only find out they're off once they're already in it, and the next dose can take up to an hour to work.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:26px; padding:34px 32px; box-shadow:0 14px 34px rgba(28,46,92,0.05);">
        <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.4px; color:#2F57E6; margin-bottom:14px;">SYMPTOM TWO · MOVEMENT</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:26px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.5px; margin:0 0 12px;">freezing of gait</h3>
        <p style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0;">the feet suddenly feel glued to the floor while the body keeps leaning forward. it strikes in doorways, on turns, and while crossing the street, a leading cause of falls and a big reason people stop leaving the house. today's cueing tools only switch on after the freeze has already started.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:19px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:600; color:#16203A; text-align:center; max-width:640px; margin:34px auto 0;">both problems take the same thing away: the ability to trust your own body in public.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <div style="max-width:980px; margin:0 auto; padding:78px 32px 30px; text-align:center;">
    <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:16px;">WHO IT'S FOR</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,5.4vw,44px); line-height:1.12; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-1.2px; margin:0 0 22px;">Built for the middle of the journey.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:20px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; max-width:680px; margin:0 auto;">Cadence is made for people in the mid-to-later stages of Parkinson's, on levodopa, living with motor fluctuations, many of them older adults. they want to keep going out, keep their independence, and stop bracing for a fall, and they're tired of dosing blind. the people around them carry that worry too, and the neurologist who sets the schedule sees them for about fifteen minutes every few months.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- CARE CIRCLE (condensed) -->
  <div style="background:#F4F7FC; border-top:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-bottom:1px solid #ECF0F7;">
    <div style="max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto; padding:80px 32px;">
      <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:48px;">
