        <div style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#A9B4C9; margin-bottom:8px;">03</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:25px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.4px; margin:0 0 10px;">Dose ahead of it</h3>
        <p style="font-size:17px; line-height:1.55; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0;">Get a nudge to take your next dose at the right moment, within your doctor's plan, to stay ahead of the dip instead of catching up after it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- THE TWO PREDICTIONS -->
  <div style="max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto; padding:70px 32px 10px;">
    <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:44px;">
      <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:14px;">THE TWO PREDICTIONS</div>
      <h2 style="font-size: clamp(28px,5.2vw,42px); line-height: 1.12; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -1.1px; margin: 0 0 16px; font-family: newsreader serif; font-style: italic">One forecast, two moments that matter.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:19px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; max-width:660px; margin:0 auto;">Both bands feed one model, and it watches for two different events, a chemical one and a mechanical one. Each gets its own early warning and its own action.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:24px; align-items:stretch;" data-stack="1">
      <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:28px; padding:36px 34px; box-shadow:0 16px 38px rgba(28,46,92,0.06);">
        <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.2px; color:#B9700F; margin-bottom:14px;">PREDICTION ONE · THE OFF WINDOW</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:24px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.4px; margin:0 0 12px;">your medication, about to wear off</h3>
        <p style="font-size:16.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0 0 20px;">as levodopa fades, stiffness, slowness and tremor creep back, and the next pill can take up to an hour to work, so finding out late means an hour of catching up.</p>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:13px;">
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;"><span style="width:22px; height:22px; flex:none; border-radius:7px; background:#FBF1E1; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-top:2px;"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 13l4 4 10-11" stroke="#B9700F" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66;">the model watches your motor trend plus the autonomic signals, heart rate, skin response, that shift before you consciously feel the dip.</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;"><span style="width:22px; height:22px; flex:none; border-radius:7px; background:#FBF1E1; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-top:2px;"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 13l4 4 10-11" stroke="#B9700F" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66;">it names a window, "off likely 11:40–12:10", tens of minutes ahead, a range you can plan around.</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;"><span style="width:22px; height:22px; flex:none; border-radius:7px; background:#FBF1E1; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-top:2px;"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 13l4 4 10-11" stroke="#B9700F" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66;">the wrist buzzes a dose nudge timed to stay ahead of it, always inside your doctor's plan.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#16203A; border-radius:28px; padding:36px 34px; box-shadow:0 16px 38px rgba(28,46,92,0.18);">
        <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.2px; color:#7CF0B7; margin-bottom:14px;">PREDICTION TWO · FREEZING OF GAIT</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:24px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.4px; margin:0 0 12px; color:#fff;">your feet, seconds before they stop</h3>
        <p style="font-size:16.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#A9B7D0; margin:0 0 20px;">a freeze doesn't come from nowhere, in the seconds before, the stride shortens and the walking rhythm breaks down. that signature is exactly what the ankle band is there to read.</p>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:13px;">
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;"><span style="width:22px; height:22px; flex:none; border-radius:7px; background:#243355; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-top:2px;"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 13l4 4 10-11" stroke="#7CF0B7" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:500; color:#C2CFE4;">the ankle pulses a steady rhythm the instant a freeze is predicted, the same walking reflex metronomes and laser shoes rely on, fired before the freeze instead of during it.</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;"><span style="width:22px; height:22px; flex:none; border-radius:7px; background:#243355; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-top:2px;"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 13l4 4 10-11" stroke="#7CF0B7" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:500; color:#C2CFE4;">the freeze model runs on the phone, not the cloud, a round trip to a server would arrive after the feet have already locked.</span></div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:12px;"><span style="width:22px; height:22px; flex:none; border-radius:7px; background:#243355; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; margin-top:2px;"><svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 13l4 4 10-11" stroke="#7CF0B7" stroke-width="2.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg></span><span style="font-size:16px; font-weight:500; color:#C2CFE4;">why it matters: freezing hits in doorways, on turns, crossing the street, it's a leading cause of falls and a big reason people stop going out.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

