  <!-- WHY MOVEMENT -->
  <div style="max-width:820px; margin:0 auto; padding:80px 32px 10px; text-align:center;">
    <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:14px;">WHY THIS IS DIFFERENT</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,5.2vw,42px); line-height:1.12; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-1.1px; margin:0 0 18px;">The body broadcasts what's coming.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:20px; line-height:1.62; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; margin:0;">Gait breaks down seconds before a freeze. Heart rate and skin response shift before an off period is felt. Fitness trackers already sit on top of these signals, they just count steps and sleep with them. Symptom diaries and clinic wearables record the hard day after it happens. Cadence reads the same skin-level signals and does the one thing none of them do: says what's about to happen, in time to act.</p>
