        </div>
        <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:26px; padding:32px 28px;">
          <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1px; color:#A9B4C9; margin-bottom:10px;">MODEL 02 · ANKLE · ON THE PHONE</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:21px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.3px; margin:0 0 10px;">freeze prediction, "is one about to start?"</h3>
          <p style="font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0 0 18px;">the differentiator. trained only on gait that still looks normal, it spots the breakdown in the seconds before the foot stops, so the ankle cue fires ahead of the freeze, not during it like today's cueing devices.</p>
          <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px; border-top:1px solid #ECF0F7; padding-top:16px;">
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">warning before the foot stops</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">~1.25s</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">improvement over starting model</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">+16% (AUC 0.70 → 0.81)</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">false alarms handled by</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">2-window confirm + lockout</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:26px; padding:32px 28px;">
          <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1px; color:#A9B4C9; margin-bottom:10px;">MODEL 03 · WRIST · SERVER-SIDE</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:21px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.3px; margin:0 0 10px;">off-window forecast, "will an off period start soon?"</h3>
          <p style="font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0 0 18px;">instead of a generic rule, cadence fits each person's real medication response curve, including how a protein-heavy meal delays absorption, and forecasts when it will drop below your personal threshold.</p>
          <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px; border-top:1px solid #ECF0F7; padding-top:16px;">
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">onset-timing error</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">33 min vs 44 for a generic rule</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">horizon</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">minutes ahead, time to act</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">measured on</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">simulated cohort · real data next</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:26px; padding:32px 28px;">
          <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1px; color:#A9B4C9; margin-bottom:10px;">MODEL 04 · PER-PERSON</div>
          <h3 style="font-size:21px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.3px; margin:0 0 10px;">personalization, "learn this specific person"</h3>
          <p style="font-size:15.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0 0 18px;">the population models are a strong starting point; one supervised calibration session tunes them to your gait, your baseline, your thresholds. the cheapest accuracy we can buy, no new dataset required.</p>
          <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px; border-top:1px solid #ECF0F7; padding-top:16px;">
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">patients improved</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">5 of 5 tested, both freeze models</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">dose-nudge timing error</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">19 → 5 min</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:12px;"><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0;">requires</span><span style="font-size:14px; font-weight:800; color:#16203A;">one supervised session at enrollment</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex; justify-content:center; gap:52px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:48px; text-align:center;">
        <div><div style="font-size:36px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-1px; font-family:'Newsreader',serif; font-style:italic;">2 cohorts</div><div style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0; margin-top:2px;">30 subjects of real freeze recordings</div></div>
        <div><div style="font-size:36px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-1px; font-family:'Newsreader',serif; font-style:italic;">384</div><div style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0; margin-top:2px;">labeled pre-freeze moments learned from</div></div>
        <div><div style="font-size:36px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:-1px; font-family:'Newsreader',serif; font-style:italic;">6–40 MB</div><div style="font-size:14px; font-weight:600; color:#8A96B0; margin-top:2px;">exported model size, fits on any phone</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- A DAY, FORECAST -->
  <div style="max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto; padding:84px 32px 10px;">
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:0.9fr 1.1fr; gap:56px; align-items:center;" data-stack="1">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:14px;">A DAY, FORECAST</div>
        <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,5vw,40px); line-height:1.12; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-1px; margin:0 0 16px;">Your medication has a shape. Cadence learns yours.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:17.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; margin:0 0 14px;">Each dose rises, peaks, and fades on a curve that's different for every person, and shifts with meals. Cadence fits that curve to your own days, so "off" stops being a surprise and becomes a place on the chart.</p>
        <p style="font-size:17.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; margin:0;">The dose nudge fires while the line is still above your threshold, because a pill taken at the crossing point is already an hour late.</p>
