  <!-- OPERATING CURVE -->
  <div style="max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto; padding:84px 32px 10px;">
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:0.9fr 1.1fr; gap:56px; align-items:center;" data-stack="1">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:14px;">THE TRADEOFF WE TUNED FOR</div>
        <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,5vw,40px); line-height:1.12; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-1px; margin:0 0 16px;">More freezes caught, fewer false alarms.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:17.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; margin:0 0 14px;">A wearable cue that cries wolf gets taken off. So the freeze predictor is judged the way it will be worn: how many freezes it warns about at a false-alarm rate a person can live with, under 2.5 per minute of walking, the shaded band.</p>
        <p style="font-size:17.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; margin:0;">In that band, the current model catches more freezes than our starting model at every point, with the warning arriving about 1.25 seconds before the foot stops.</p>
      </div>
