        <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:64px 1fr; gap:22px; background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:24px; padding:28px 30px;" data-roadmap-row="1">
          <div style="width:52px; height:52px; border-radius:16px; background:#16203A; color:#7CF0B7; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:19px; font-weight:800;">1</div>
          <div>
            <div style="display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;"><h3 style="font-size:20px; font-weight:800; margin:0 0 8px;">pair the bands, day one</h3><span style="font-size:13px; font-weight:700; color:#8A96B0;">YOU, AT HOME</span></div>
            <p style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0;">both bands connect to the phone over bluetooth. the freeze models load onto the phone itself, from the first walk, detection runs locally, because a trip to a server would arrive after the feet have already stopped.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:64px 1fr; gap:22px; background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:24px; padding:28px 30px;" data-roadmap-row="1">
          <div style="width:52px; height:52px; border-radius:16px; background:#16203A; color:#7CF0B7; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; font-size:19px; font-weight:800;">2</div>
          <div>
            <div style="display:flex; align-items:baseline; gap:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;"><h3 style="font-size:20px; font-weight:800; margin:0 0 8px;">one calibration session, week one</h3><span style="font-size:13px; font-weight:700; color:#8A96B0;">YOU + YOUR CLINICIAN</span></div>
            <p style="font-size:16px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0;">a supervised walking session, guided in the app, gives the models a labeled sample of <em>your</em> gait and <em>your</em> freezes. from it, cadence tunes both freeze models to you, fits your personal medication response curve, and sets your off-threshold. in testing this single session improved every patient it was tried on.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
