  <!-- WHAT'S NEW / TWO LAYERS -->
  <div style="max-width:1100px; margin:0 auto; padding:90px 32px;">
    <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:46px;">
      <div style="font-size:15px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:{{ accent }}; margin-bottom:14px;">HONESTLY, WHAT'S NEW</div>
      <h2 style="font-size:clamp(28px,5.2vw,42px); line-height:1.12; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-1.1px; margin:0 0 18px;">Detection is established. Acting on the forecast is the part no one has shipped.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:19px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#3A4A66; max-width:680px; margin:0 auto;">There are two layers in Cadence, and only the top one is new. We're specific about that on purpose.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:24px; align-items:stretch;" data-stack="1">
      <div style="background:#fff; border:1px solid #ECF0F7; border-radius:28px; padding:36px 34px;">
        <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.2px; color:#8A96B0; margin-bottom:14px;">BASE LAYER · DETECTION</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:23px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.4px; margin:0 0 12px;">scoring symptoms minute to minute</h3>
        <p style="font-size:16.5px; line-height:1.6; font-weight:500; color:#536084; margin:0;">calling the on/off state from sensor signals is established, well-trodden research. it's the foundation cadence stands on, not the part we claim to have invented.*</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#16203A; border:1px solid #16203A; border-radius:28px; padding:36px 34px;">
        <div style="font-size:13px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.2px; color:#7CF0B7; margin-bottom:14px;">TOP LAYER · FORECASTING + ACTION</div>
        <h3 style="font-size:23px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:-0.4px; margin:0 0 12px; color:#fff;">turning the forecast into a decision</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.6; font-weight: 700; color: #A9B7D0; margin: 0">predicting the next off window and the pre-freeze moment, then turning each into a just-in-time dose nudge and a preemptive cue, inside one screenless two-sensor product. that closed loop, to the patient, is the part no one has built.*</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:15px; line-height:1.65; font-weight:500; color:#8A96B0; text-align:center; max-width:700px; margin:28px auto 0;">research has shown off episodes and freezes can be predicted to a degree, small studies have forecast wearing-off from wearable and autonomic signals, and pre-freeze prediction has reached the mid-eighties in sensitivity. cadence doesn't claim to invent prediction. our goal is to develop a personalized system that turns the forecast into an action, for the patient, instead of stopping at a report for the doctor. <br><br>*this technology requires time to learn your personal signals.</p>
